text: Dale Arnold Jarrett (born November 26, 1956) is a retired American racecar driver. Jarret used to drive in the Monster Energy NASCAR Cup Series. He won the 1999 Winston Cup championship and the 1993 Daytona 500. Jarrett has been called one of NASCAR's 50 greatest drivers. Jarrett retired in 2008 and now does Commentary for NBC. His father is NASCAR legend Ned Jarrett. ==References== Category:NASCAR drivers Category:1956 births Category:Living people Category:Daytona 500 winners Category:American racecar drivers Category:Sportspeople from North Carolina
